<subSubSection id="21E86513FFF75F53FCC7F9947E4AB5EE" pageId="5" pageNumber="400" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF75F53FCC7F9947E4AB5EE" blockId="5.[756,1233,1604,1855]" pageId="5" pageNumber="400">
E t y m o l o g y. From the Latin words “ 
<emphasis id="5B86EA8AFFF75F53FCBEF9B47E8CB52F" box="[848,916,1636,1662]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="400">brevis</emphasis>
” — short, and “ 
<emphasis id="5B86EA8AFFF75F53FBB8F9B579B9B52F" box="[1110,1185,1637,1662]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="400">scapus</emphasis>
” — scape, meaning that the antennal scape is short.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="21E86513FFF75F5CFCC7F9147F9DB27B" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="405" pageId="5" pageNumber="400" type="description">
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF75F50FCC7F9147EB6B6B2" blockId="5.[756,1233,1604,1855]" lastBlockId="6.[166,1225,1192,1859]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="401" pageId="5" pageNumber="400">
W o r k e r (
<figureCitation id="F1C92A1DFFF75F53FC5EF914793CB58E" box="[944,1060,1732,1759]" captionStart-0="Figs 7–8" captionStart-1="Figs 9–11" captionStartId-0="6.[170,209,1082,1104]" captionStartId-1="7.[174,213,1774,1796]" captionTargetBox-0="[189,1190,179,1041]" captionTargetBox-1="[212,1219,370,1696]" captionTargetId-0="figure-259@6.[128,1262,171,1045]" captionTargetId-1="figure-11@7.[182,1223,341,1715]" captionTargetPageId-0="6" captionTargetPageId-1="7" captionText-0="Figs 7–8. Eocenomyrma breviscapa sp. n., photos of holotype worker: 7 — body in dorsal view; 8 — body in lateral view. Scale bar 1 mm." captionText-1="Figs 9–11. Eocenomyrma breviscapa sp. n., line drawings of holotype worker made based on photos: 9 — body in dorsal view; 10 — body in lateral view; 11 — head in dorsal view (sculpture omitted). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449292" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449294" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6449292/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6449294/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="400">figs 7–11</figureCitation>
). Total length ca. 
<quantity id="AE0A9B7DFFF75F53FCC8F9347E97B5AE" box="[806,911,1764,1791]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="400" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
. Head short, 1.07 times longer than width, with convex sides, rounded occipital corners and convex occipital margin. Eyes of moderate size, their maximum diameter 0.21 of head length, situated at midlength of lateral sided of head. Antennae 12-segmented, with distinct, quite big 3-segmented club that is subequal to total length of remainder funicular segments, first funicular segment ca. 1.5 times longer than width, 2–8th segments transversal; scape very short, nearly twice shorter than head length, far not reaching occipital margin. Central part of clypeus longitudinally concave, with two lateral longitudinal carinae and well marked anterolateral corners, its anterior margin concave, with pair of long setae on anterolateral corners. Clypeus posteriorly widely inserted between frontal lobes; frontal lobes anteriorly reaching anterior clypeal margin. Palp formula 4, 3. Mandibles elongate-triangular, masticatory margin with longer apical tooth and small 5 denticles.
</paragraph>
<caption id="3D8D6610FFF75F53FF40F90B7F16B477" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6462414" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6462414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6462414/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="400" startId="5.[174,207,1755,1777]" targetBox="[174,719,767,1738]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF75F53FF40F90B7F16B477" blockId="5.[174,718,1755,1830]" pageId="5" pageNumber="400">
Fig. 6. 
<taxonomicName id="AEF24D1BFFF75F53FF18F90B7CFBB5A1" authority="Radchenko &amp; Dlussky, 2016" authorityName="Radchenko &amp; Dlussky" authorityYear="2016" box="[246,483,1755,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Eocenomyrma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="400" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ukrainica" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="5B86EA8AFFF75F53FF18F90B7CFBB5A1" box="[246,483,1755,1776]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="400">Eocenomyrma ukrainica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="40B557F1FFF75F53FE00F90B7F3EB5A0" box="[494,550,1755,1777]" pageId="5" pageNumber="400" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, line drawing of 
<typeStatus id="B649883AFFF75F53FF40F9257C1AB45A" box="[174,258,1781,1803]" pageId="5" pageNumber="400">paratype</typeStatus>
gyne made based on photo, body in lateral view (sculpture omitted). Scale bar 
<quantity id="AE0A9B7DFFF75F53FE21F8C07F12B477" box="[463,522,1808,1830]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="400" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="3D8D6610FFF45F50FF44FBEA7CA4B73A" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449292" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6449292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449292/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" startId="6.[170,209,1082,1104]" targetBox="[189,1190,179,1041]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF45F50FF44FBEA7CA4B73A" blockId="6.[170,1229,1082,1131]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">
Figs 7–8. 
<taxonomicName id="AEF24D1BFFF45F50FEE6FBEB7CE4B71E" authority="Radchenko &amp; Dlussky, 2016" authorityName="Radchenko &amp; Dlussky" authorityYear="2016" box="[264,508,1082,1104]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Eocenomyrma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviscapa" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="5B86EA8AFFF45F50FEE6FBEB7CE4B71E" box="[264,508,1082,1104]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">Eocenomyrma breviscapa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="40B557F1FFF45F50FDEDFBEA7F21B701" box="[515,569,1082,1104]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, photos of holotype worker: 7 — body in dorsal view; 8 — body in lateral view. Scale bar 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF45F50FF35FA387C5DB452" blockId="6.[166,1225,1192,1859]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">
Mesosoma ca. 2.8 times longer than height, promesonotal suture developed, metanotal groove deep. Anterior margin of pronotum slightly convex, humeri narrowly rounded. Propodeal spines rather short, straight, widened at base and acute at apex, directed posteriorly at an angle ca. 45 
<superScript id="9E879BD0FFF45F50FE10F9977F1FB504" attach="left" box="[510,519,1607,1621]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">o</superScript>
(seen in profile), very slightly divergent (seen from above). Propodeal lobes rounded. Petiole with very short peduncle, quite high, only little longer than height, its anterior surface steep, very slightly concave, meets with dorsal surface of node at an acute angle, dorsal plate short ant strongly declined posteriorly so that petiole seems cuneiform (seen in profile). Postpetiole wider than petiole. Middle and hind tibiae without spur.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF45F50FF35F8D87CBFB412" blockId="6.[166,1225,1192,1859]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">Head dorsum, mesosoma and waist densely punctated, head dorsum additionally with longitudinal striation.</paragraph>
<caption id="3D8D6610FFF55F51FF40F93E798CB44F" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449294" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6449294" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449294/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="402" startId="7.[174,213,1774,1796]" targetBox="[212,1219,370,1696]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF55F51FF40F93E798CB44F" blockId="7.[174,1232,1774,1822]" pageId="7" pageNumber="402">
Figs 9–11. 
<taxonomicName id="AEF24D1BFFF55F51FEFBF93E7F1FB452" authority="Radchenko &amp; Dlussky, 2016" authorityName="Radchenko &amp; Dlussky" authorityYear="2016" box="[277,519,1774,1795]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Eocenomyrma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviscapa" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="5B86EA8AFFF55F51FEFBF93E7F1FB452" box="[277,519,1774,1795]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="402">Eocenomyrma breviscapa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="40B557F1FFF55F51FDE3F93E7F59B455" box="[525,577,1774,1796]" pageId="7" pageNumber="402" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, line drawings of holotype worker made based on photos: 9 — body in dorsal view; 10 — body in lateral view; 11 — head in dorsal view (sculpture omitted). Scale bar 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="3D8D6610FFFA5F5EFF44F90E79BDB45E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449296" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6449296" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449296/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="403" startId="8.[170,209,1758,1780]" targetBox="[220,1213,213,1708]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph id="694D3698FFFA5F5EFF44F90E79BDB45E" blockId="8.[170,1217,1758,1807]" pageId="8" pageNumber="403">
Figs 12–13. Line drawings of 
<taxonomicName id="AEF24D1BFFFA5F5EFE27F90F7E39B5A5" authority="(Mayr)" baseAuthorityName="Mayr" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[457,801,1758,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Eocenomyrma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosostriata">
<emphasis id="5B86EA8AFFFA5F5EFE27F90F7FCCB5A5" box="[457,724,1759,1780]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="403">Eocenomyrma rugosostriata</emphasis>
(Mayr)
</taxonomicName>
, neotype worker (12, body in dorso-lateral view) and 
<taxonomicName id="AEF24D1BFFFA5F5EFEE0F92A7F7EB45E" authority="Dlussky et Radchenko" authorityName="Dlussky et Radchenko" authorityYear="2006" box="[270,614,1785,1807]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Eocenomyrma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegantula">
<emphasis id="5B86EA8AFFFA5F5EFEE0F92A7C03B45E" box="[270,283,1786,1807]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="403">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5B86EA8AFFFA5F5EFEC8F9297C90B45F" box="[294,392,1785,1806]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="403">elegantula</emphasis>
Dlussky et Radchenko
</taxonomicName>
, holotype worker (13, body in lateral view). Scale bar 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="694D3698FFFB5F5FFF0DFF7F7C8FB3BB" blockId="9.[174,1233,175,330]" pageId="9" pageNumber="404">Body with sparse, rather short, blunt straight suberect hairs, scape and legs with decumbent pilosity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="694D3698FFFB5F5FFF0DFF3F7FEDB21B" blockId="9.[174,1233,175,330]" pageId="9" pageNumber="404">
